, slide-mounted adult female. Scale bar = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="AF88AFB5FFABFF8CFF62FEC5FB0199D9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6416907" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6416907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6416907/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" startId="5.[151,264,1716,1740]" targetBox="[162,1433,195,1686]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="FB48FF3DFFABFF8CFF62FEC5FB0199D9" blockId="5.[151,1437,1716,1777]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFF62FEC5FE9599E5" bold="true" box="[151,325,1716,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">FIGURES 8–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3CF784BEFFABFF8CFEBFFEC4FD5F99E5" authority="Tian &amp; Xing, 2022" authorityName="Tian &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2022" box="[330,655,1717,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" genus="Unachionaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multiglandularis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFEBFFEC4FD5F99E5" box="[330,655,1717,1741]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">Unachionaspis multiglandularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFD66FEC4FD1A99E5" bold="true" box="[659,714,1717,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D2B09E54FFABFF8CFD66FEC4FD1A99E5" box="[659,714,1717,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, slide-mounted adult female. 
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFC04FEC4FBD499E5" bold="true" box="[1009,1028,1717,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">8.</emphasis>
Slide-mounted adult female; 
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFADCFEC4FAEC99E5" bold="true" box="[1321,1340,1717,1741]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">9.</emphasis>
Antenna; 
<emphasis id="C983232FFFABFF8CFF62FEA8FF6799D9" bold="true" box="[151,183,1753,1777]" pageId="5" pageNumber="525">10.</emphasis>
